# рџЌ… StudyWithMe

**StudyWithMe** is a native iOS app built with SwiftUI to manage study sessions, track goals, and monitor progress using the **Pomodoro technique**.

-----

## вњЁ Key Features

The app is organized into four main sections accessible via the Tab Bar:

### вЏ±пёЏ Timer (Pomodoro)

- Custom `CircularProgressView` with gradients and smooth animations
- Full Pomodoro logic: focus sessions, short breaks, and long breaks
- **Severe Mode** вЂ” cancels the current session if the user exits the app while the timer is running

### рџЋЇ Goals

- Set study goals with a title and a target number of Pomodoros to complete
- Visual progress indicators for every active goal
- Edit goals via a modal sheet (title and Pomodoro target)
- Goals and completion status saved locally with `UserDefaults`

### рџ“– History

- Full log of all completed study sessions
- Each entry shows activity description, duration (in minutes), and date
- Tap to edit session details or swipe to delete
- User-friendly empty state when no sessions have been recorded

### вљ™пёЏ Settings

- Configurable durations for Pomodoro, Short Break, and Long Break using Steppers
- Adjustable number of Pomodoros before a Long Break
- Toggle for **Severe Mode**

-----

## рџ› пёЏ Architecture & Tech Stack

The project follows the **MVVM** pattern to cleanly separate business logic from the UI.

|Layer       |Technology                                     |
|------------|-----------------------------------------------|
|Language    |Swift 5+                                       |
|UI Framework|SwiftUI (NavigationStack, TabView)             |
|Reactive    |Combine (@Published, ObservableObject)         |
|Persistence |UserDefaults + JSON encoding/decoding (Codable)|
|Extensions  |Live Activity via TimerActivityExtension       |

-----

## рџ“‹ Requirements

- iOS 16.0+
- Xcode 15+

-----

## рџљЂ Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Marcelloguida00/StudyWithMe.git
cd StudyWithMe
```

### 2. Open in Xcode

```bash
open StudyWithMe.xcodeproj
```

### 3. Build and run

Select a Simulator or physical device with iOS 16+ and hit `Product в†’ Run`.

> No external dependencies or API keys required.

